a state appeals court ruled yesterday against police officers who charged the abc network 's primetime live of defaming them as racists on national television the court ruled that the officers traffic stop of three black men was unlawful and that the commentary was not defamatory the 1996 program on racial profiling narrated by diane sawyer used a hidden camera to show officers louis hornberger robert tonkery and james mennuti as they stopped and interrogated the black men neville l johnson the lawyer for the officers said the issue was not whether the search was unlawful but whether the officers made a profile stop stacy albin nyt

